net.metro.systemobjects.periodobjects

Class Day

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.metro.systemobjects.periodobjects.Day

  • public class Day
extends java.lang.Object
    Object to represent a day of the week. The only way to access a member of this class is through one of the static fields, since the days of the week cannot change.
    Author:
    Sean Harger

      • Day

        private Day(int sq,
   java.lang.String nm)
        Constructs a Day object. Since this is a private constructor, the only day objects that are accessible are those that are members of the static fields of the Day class.
        Parameters:
        sq - integer sequence of this day during the week (Monday is 1, Tuesday is 2, etc.)
        nm - name of the day

        public static boolean areDaysEqual(java.util.List<Day> listOne,
                   java.util.List<Day> listTwo)

        Parameters:
